Someone came to fix the floor in my kitchen, so I'm going to pretend I still have work to do and work from home while reviewing Too Hot to Handle.
If I can manage to open this cursed file. (Damn OneDrive.)
*pirate voice* I'm there.
And that's where he starts to really break through. Awesome!
His passive-aggressive way of cranking my air purifier all the way makes me uncomfortable, but it smells like sawdust, so it's justified even though it's an anti-mask. And besides, I really need to protect myself, right??
I really want to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
The positive thing is that I've finished rereading chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but there's a big suspense. Good work.
In the middle of doing find-and-replace on ... ➡️ ellipsis character, and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But anyway, I stick to it. The most natural speeches are usually fragmented, especially when people let themselves go with their emotions.
The craftsman is vacuuming, and with a bit of luck, he will soon be finished.
He came out (as far as I heard) to cut something. So I took a look to see where he was. It's far from being done :(
More than 7 pages on chapter five. It remains my favorite chapter, and it's quite well-developed. Just some layout adjustments and minor changes to switch to the active voice and improve conciseness. That said, I would really like a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still tinkering in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. I hope that's a good sign.
The craftsman has left!
He told me he had done an estimate for the whole floor, but the owners were cheap and only paid for the small damaged area near the door. It's definitely better now.
The house is airing out, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I enjoy a cup of tea in the garden!
